(The Professors Academy Website
Complete Project Overview

1. Project Identity

Project Name:
The Professors Academy Website

Project Type:
Custom academic institution website with an integrated admin panel, online admission management, public announcements, results publishing, faculty management, visitor messaging, analytics, SEO support, dark mode, live website sync, and downloadable admission forms.

Primary Goal:
To provide a professional and easy-to-manage academy website where:
- students can submit enrollment forms online,
- website visitors can send direct messages through the public website,
- the academy can manage admissions from an admin panel,
- announcements and results can be published,
- faculty profiles can be managed,
- students can track their admission status,
- the institution can maintain a premium online presence with minimal deployment complexity.


2. Main Modules

Public Website:
- Home section
- Enrollment section
- Status Check section
- Message Us section
- Faculty section
- Results section
- Announcements section
- Gallery section
- FAQ section
- About Us section
- Floating contact buttons
- Splash screen
- SEO, indexing, and PWA support

Admin Panel:
- Secure login
- Dashboard and website insights
- Pending admissions management
- Final admission records
- Website messages inbox
- Announcements management
- Results management
- Faculty management
- Website settings and content editing
- Gallery and FAQ management
- Activity log
- Backup and restore tools
- Motion/effects control
- Dark mode control
- Public status-check control


3. Technology Stack

Frontend:
- HTML5
- CSS3
- Vanilla JavaScript

Backend:
- Python
- Flask
- Werkzeug

Server / Runtime:
- Gunicorn for deployment
- Flask app for routing, APIs, admin rendering, validation, and business logic

Database:
- SQLite

Deployment / Hosting Compatibility:
- Localhost / local Flask server
- Railway
- Shared hosting with Python support
- Apache-compatible hosting \(optional .htaccess included\)


4. Languages Used

Programming Languages:
- Python
- JavaScript

Markup / Styling:
- HTML
- CSS

Data / Config Formats:
- JSON
- SQLite SQL schema
- XML \(sitemaps\)
- TXT \(robots.txt style output and project docs\)


5. Core Public Features

Homepage:
- Premium academic hero section
- Editable hero text from admin panel
- Academy splash screen on website load
- Quick statistics
- Latest announcements preview
- Smooth formal motion effects
- Gallery section
- FAQ section
- Homepage blocks on/off control
- Live content refresh without manual page refresh

Enrollment Form:
- Full Name
- Father Name
- Mobile No
- Father Contact No
- CNIC No with formatting
- Gender
- Email Address
- Date of Birth
- Date of Birth in DD/MM/YYYY format
- Passport Size Picture upload
- Class selection
- Group selection where applicable
- Subject selection based on class/group
- Address
- Client-side and server-side validation
- Cropping support for photo upload
- Success popup after submission

Status Check:
- Student can check status using CNIC No and Date of Birth
- Date of Birth support in DD/MM/YYYY format
- Status popup
- Admission-form PDF download when eligible
- Admin can disable status checking and publish a custom disabled message

Faculty:
- Filtered public faculty display
- Separate filtering for:
  - Class IX-X
  - XI-XII Pre-Med
  - XI-XII Pre-Eng
  - MDCAT
  - ECAT
- Teacher photo, subject, qualification, and experience
- One teacher can be assigned to multiple class sections from admin
- Public faculty cards show only the relevant section inside each active filter

Results:
- Public result cards
- Downloadable PDF result files
- Optional "New" badge per result

Announcements:
- Public notices
- Optional "New" badge per announcement

Message Us:
- Public message form with full name, email, mobile number, and message body
- Message length control
- Messages delivered to the admin panel inbox
- Admin can mark messages handled or delete them

About Section:
- Contact numbers
- Email
- Office timing
- Address
- Google map
- Academy location highlight

Floating Buttons:
- WhatsApp floating button
- Facebook floating button


6. Core Admin Features

Admin Access:
- Custom secure admin URL
- Username/password login
- Session-based authentication

Dashboard:
- Quick action shortcuts
- Statistics
- Website insights
- Live visitors information
- Activity log summary
- Instant refresh of new admissions and website messages

Pending Admissions:
- Search and filters
- Bulk actions
- Approve
- Reject
- Delete
- Export selected list

Admission Records:
- Confirmed and rejected records
- Class-wise sections
- Time-range filters
- Totals by class and status
- CSV exports

Announcements Management:
- Add announcement
- Edit announcement
- Delete announcement
- Draft / Live mode
- New badge control
- Marquee control

Results Management:
- Add result
- Edit result
- Delete result
- Draft / Live mode
- New badge control
- File upload support

Faculty Management:
- Add faculty
- Edit faculty
- Delete faculty
- Photo upload with crop support
- Old faculty photo remove / replace option while editing
- Faculty section and group assignment
- Multiple section assignment for one teacher
- Experience field
- Ordering support

Website Settings:
- Contact details
- Address
- Office timing
- Facebook page URL
- WhatsApp button controls
- Public status-check controls
- Homepage hero content
- Enrollment section content
- Gallery section content
- FAQ section content
- Homepage section on/off controls
- Popup notice content
- Status popup messages
- Downloaded form note
- Class admission visibility scope
- Animation / effects toggle
- Public dark mode toggle
- Public message form toggle
- Facebook and WhatsApp controls

Backup & Restore:
- Backup download
- Restore from backup

Activity Log:
- Tracks important admin-side actions


7. Database Design

Database Engine:
- SQLite

Main Database File:
- database.db

Primary Tables:
- students
- announcements
- results
- faculty
- admin
- settings
- analytics / tracking related tables
- activity log related tables

Students Table Stores:
- student identity details
- contacts
- CNIC
- DOB
- class / group / subjects
- photo path
- roll number
- admission status
- confirmation / rejection times

Announcements Table Stores:
- title
- description
- date
- live/draft status
- new badge state

Results Table Stores:
- title
- class
- year
- uploaded PDF filename
- live/draft status
- new badge state

Faculty Table Stores:
- teacher name
- subject
- qualification
- photo
- class/section assignment
- track/group
- experience
- display order

Settings Table Stores:
- public website editable content
- contact values
- WhatsApp / Facebook values
- popup settings
- marquee settings
- motion settings
- class-visibility settings


8. Roll Number Logic

Roll numbers are generated in structured academic format:
- current year / class / roll no
- current year / class / group / roll no
- current year / MDCAT or ECAT / roll no

Examples:
- 2k26/IX/001
- 2k26/X/001
- 2k26/XI/P.M/001
- 2k26/XI/P.E/001
- 2k26/MDCAT/001
- 2k26/ECAT/001


