18. Deployment Notes

Recommended for Hosting:
- set SECRET_KEY
- set admin username/password
- use persistent storage for SQLite and uploads
- redeploy after pushing latest source

Recommended Environment Values:
- SECRET_KEY
- TPA_ADMIN_USERNAME
- TPA_ADMIN_PASSWORD
- TPA_SECURE_COOKIES=1
- TPA_DATA_DIR=/data \(for persistent hosted storage\)


19. Project Strengths

- Minimal file structure
- Strong admin control
- Editable content without code changes
- Academic branding
- Public + admin workflow in one project
- Real student admission handling
- Downloadable formal forms
- Good deployment portability
- SEO and analytics support


20. Final Technical Summary

This project is a full academy management website built with:
- HTML
- CSS
- JavaScript
- Python
- Flask
- SQLite
- Gunicorn

It combines:
- a public academic website,
- a secure admin panel,
- online enrollment processing,
- result and announcement publishing,
- faculty directory management,
- website content editing,
- analytics,
- SEO,
- file uploads,
- and PDF-based admission-document support.

In short:
This is not just a simple website. It is a complete custom academic web application for admissions, communication, and academy operations.
) Tj
